The steady-state absorbance spectra (Fig. 1a) exhibit an absorption onset at ~1.6 eV and a monotonic increase with photon energy. These features agree with reports on the same compound24 and their relatives (MAPbI3)25. Yang et al. employed a detailed model, based on Elliot’s theory26, to analyze both the steady-state and transient absorption spectra, assuming both the conduction band and valence band possess parabolic dispersion4,27. Thereafter, many works follow the same parabolic-band assumption in their fits to steady-state absorption, and subsequent transient absorption data analysis21,22.Fig. 1Steady-state absorption spectrum measurement.
